cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with person re-identification using deep learning models and discusses the vulnerability of these models to adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the security implications of the vulnerability of deep re-ID models, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of adversarial examples, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of the proposed attack algorithm on datasets, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
